      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "There's a `~` there already indicating \"approximately\", synchronizing headers is fast anyway -- at 1M headers, 0.01% is 100 headers or 8000 bytes so should take a trivial amount of time to download/validate, and 100 headers is much smaller than how many headers are downloaded at once in general. This doesn't seem worthwhile to me.",
